Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7. Boil a full #kettle{}.

Chop the @Potatoes{450%grams} into 2cm chunks (peel first if you prefer). Peel the @Garlic Clove{2}.

Pour the boiled water into a large #saucepan{} on high heat with @salt{1/2%tsp}. Add the potatoes and peeled garlic to the water and cook until just tender, ~{12-14%mins}.

While the potatoes boil, chop the @Sweet Potato{2} into 2cm wide wedges (no need to peel).

Pop the wedges onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with oil, season with salt and pepper, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary. Set aside for now.

Cut the @Lime{1} into wedges.

Just before the potatoes finish boiling, add the sweet potato wedges to the oven and roast on the middle shelf until golden, ~{30-35%mins}. Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, in a large #bowl{}, combine the @Orkney Crab Meat{100%grams}, a good squeeze of lime juice, the @Red Thai Style Paste{50%grams}, @Thai Style Spice Mix{1%sachet} and @Breadcrumbs{50%grams}. Season with salt and pepper. Mix together well.

Once the potatoes are cooked, drain and allow to steam uncovered for ~{2%mins}. Return to the pan, off the heat.

Mash the potatoes and garlic with a #potato masher{}, ensuring the mixture isn't too smooth so that some small chunks of potato remain. Stir the potatoes into the crab mixture. Mix together well.

Allow the mixture to cool slightly, then shape into 3cm thick patties, 3 per person. Transfer the crab cakes to a large, lined baking tray. Drizzle over some oil then bake on the top shelf of your oven until golden, ~{24-26%mins}. Gently turn halfway.

While the crab cakes bake, trim and peel the @Carrot{1}. Use the #peeler{} to peel long ribbons down the length of the carrot, stopping at the core.

In a small bowl, mix together the @Sweet Chilli Sauce{48%grams} and @Mayonnaise{2%tbsp}. Set aside for now.

Give your large bowl a quick wash, then add the @Sambal Paste{15%grams}, a good squeeze of lime juice, the @Sugar for the Dressing{1%tsp} and @Olive Oil for the Dressing{1%tbsp}. Season with salt and pepper.

> While you're waiting for everything to cook, do the washing up.

Just before everything's ready, add the carrot and @Baby Leaf Mix{50%grams} to the dressing and toss to coat.

Share the crab cakes between your plates and drizzle over the sweet chilli mayo.

Serve the salad and sweet potato wedges alongside.

Enjoy!